quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
25,44,"Do you think that most of them hear or understand? For they are merely like cattle; nay, even worse than them. {1}",footnotes:1:They are only like the cattle because they follow their lusts blindly. Just as the sheep and cattle do not know where their driver is taking them
25,45,"Have you not seen how your Lord spreads the shade? If He will, He could have made it stationary; instead, We have made the sun its pilot. {1}",footnotes:1:The word dalil has been used in the sense of the pilot
25,46,"So (as the sun rises), We gradually roll up that shade unto Us. {1}",footnotes:1:We annihilate it or cause it to disappear
25,47,"It is Allah Who has made night a garment for you, {1} and sleep the repose (of death), and has made day the time of rising to life. {2}",footnotes:1:The night is a garment in the sense that it covers and hides things.This verse has three objects:
25,48,"And He it is Who sends forth the winds as glad tidings, heralding His Mercy. Then We send down pure water {1} from the sky",footnotes:1:That is
25,49,"that We may revive through it a dead land and give it for drink to many cattle and human beings from among Our creation. {1}",footnotes:1:This verse also gives proofs of the doctrine of Tauhid and the Hereafter. Besides
25,50,"We present this wondrous phenomenon to them over and over again {1} that they may learn a lesson from it. But most people simply decline everything except disbelief and ingratitude. {2}",footnotes:1:“We have repeated it among them” may have three meanings:(1) We have cited the phenomenon of rainfall over and over again in the Quran in order to make plain to them the reality.
25,51,"Had We so willed, We would have raised up in every town a warner. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
25,52,"So, (O Prophet), do not follow the unbelievers but engage in a mighty striving against them with this Qur'an."
25,53,"And He it is Who has joined the two seas: one sweet and palatable and the other saltish and bitter; and He has set a barrier and an insurmountable obstruction between the two that keeps them apart. {1}",footnotes:1:This phenomenon has been perceived in many places in the sea and on the land that sweet water and bitter water has existed side by side. Turkish Admiral Syedi Ali Rais
25,54,"And He it is Who has created man from water and then produced from him two sorts of kindred: by descent and by marriage. Your Lord is All-Powerful. {1}",footnotes:1:Here the miracle of the birth of man from a mere sperm drop and the procreation of his offspring from man and woman have been cited as a proof of Tauhid. Though both man and woman belong to the same genus
25,55,"And yet people worship deities other than Allah that can neither benefit them nor hurt them. Besides, the unbeliever is ever prone to come to the support of everyone who rebels against his Lord. {1}",footnotes:1:This is a characteristic of the typical disbeliever. He is a helper and defender of all those who are rebels against Allah and an enemy of all those who may he striving to raise Allah’s Word and enforce His Law in the world. He is associated directly or indirectly with all the works of Allah’s disobedience and opposes and resists in one way or the other every effort that is made to bring people to the path of Allah’s obedience and service.
